rComments: She asks a lot of content-oriented questions in hopes of stimulating class discussion when it actually makes the classes a bit dry. However, listen carefully to her analysis of events and theories; she has a lot of insight and knowledge on Asian politics. Also, in-class debates were occasionally very fun. Overall, a decent class.
Her lectures are either interesting or dry. There are quite a lot of concepts, but most seem easy. There is a coursepack, but the readings aren't too dry.
